content:
Main Structure A web page is a list of nested tags that respects a the HTML syntax.
Each website has a main the following structure.
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8  &lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;title&gt;My website&lt;/title&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt; put your content here &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt;    &lt;html&gt; &lt;/html&gt;
It declares the document as a web page. All the other tags must be inside it. &lt;head&gt; &lt;/head&gt;
This tag contains the information (metadata) about the author, the description of the web page,&hellip;
The head tag is not visible in the page. &lt;title&gt; &lt;/title&gt;
The title of the page that appear in the browser tab. &lt;body&gt; &lt;/body&gt;
This is where the page content goes.  Most used tags These are the main HTML tags that are used to create a website.
    Code Example     Sections     New page division &lt;div&gt;This is a division&lt;/div&gt; This is a division   Paragraph &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph&lt;/p&gt; This is a paragraph
   New line &lt;p&gt; New &lt;br/&gt; line &lt;/p&gt;  New  line    Text formatting     Header 1 &lt;h1&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt;  Title   Header ? (2-&gt;6) &lt;h?&gt;&lt;/h?&gt;  header 5   Bold &lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;  bold text   Italic &lt;i&gt; italic text&lt;/i&gt;  italic text   Media &amp; buttons     Button &lt;button&gt;This is a button&lt;/button&gt; This is a button   Link anchor &lt;a href=&quot;link&quot;&gt;text description&lt;/a&gt; Please click me   Image &lt;img src=&quot;Image_URL&quot; width=&quot;XXXpx&quot; height=&quot;XXXpx&quot;&gt;    Lists     Unordered list &lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;item1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;item2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;  first item  second item    Ordered list &lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;item1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;item2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;  first item  second item     Sources  http://www.simplehtmlguide.com/examplesheet.php https://htmlcheatsheet.com/
